one_reviews_text: Quite a pleasant view of some kinda fort in the desert. It looked good and the sun was very bright.

Nice experience in an empty desert. But very well done, the way the sun blinds you when entering the court jard from a part of the museum.  It is a small experience, but a diamond for that. Look at the sky and see the clouds slowly move above you. This is not a still; it is a living place in a silent world.
And nice for history buffs, too. But, that thing with the sea? Which sea?
I would have liked to have been able to read the signs, but the text was too small.
